    "explanation": "Step 1: This is a telescoping series: each term cancels the next.\nStep 2: (1−√2)+(√2−√3)+...+(√15−√16) — all middle terms cancel.\nStep 3: What remains: 1 − √16 = 1 − 4 = −3.\nFinal Answer: -3"
  },
  {
    "id": "ssc_2016_q377",
    "question": "The average salary of male employees in a firm was Rs. 5200 and that of females was Rs. 4200. The mean salary of all the employees was Rs. 5000. What is the % of female employees? Rs. 5200 Rs. 4200 | Rs. 5000 , ?",
    "options": {
      "A": "80%",
      "B": "20%",
      "C": "40%",
      "D": "30%"
    },
    "correctAnswer": "B",
    "correctValue": "20%",
    "difficulty": "hard",
    "topic": "average",
    "year": 2016,
    "exam": "SSC CGL",
    "explanation": "Step 1: Weighted avg: 5200.0×(male%) + 4200.0×(female%) = 5000.0. Let female% = p.\nStep 2: 5200.0×(1−p/100) + 4200.0×(p/100) = 5000.0.\nStep 3: (5200.0−4200.0)×(1−p/100) = 5000.0−4200.0 → p = (5200.0−5000.0)/(5200.0−4200.0)×100 = 20%.\nFinal Answer: 20%"
  },
